The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 BC Roy notice

 New Delhi, Nov. 15: The National Human Rights Commission today asked the Bengal government to respond to reports on lack of facilities and equipment at Calcuttas BC Roy Memorial Hospital for Children, where 22 infants died in three days.

 It also sought the chief secretarys comment on a report which quoted the medical superintendent of the hospital as saying that the deaths are a coincidence.

 Newspapers had quoted the superintendent as saying that the deaths had occurred in the neonatal ward and most of the babies were newborn and underweight and had died due to septicaemia. 




